<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.0" id="MathArtLogic">
  <title>Arithmetic and Logic Operations</title>

  <para>
    Opcodes that perform arithmetic and logic operations are 
    <link linkend="subtracts"><citetitle>-</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="adds"><citetitle>+</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="opand"><citetitle>&amp;&amp;</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="opor"><citetitle>||</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="multiplies"><citetitle>*</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="divides"><citetitle>/</citetitle></link>, 
    <link linkend="raises"><citetitle>^</citetitle></link>, and 
    <link linkend="modulus"><citetitle>%</citetitle></link>.
  </para>
  <para>
    See the <link linkend="ControlConditional"><citetitle>Conditional Values</citetitle></link> section and the <link linkend="if"><citetitle>if</citetitle></link> family of opcodes for usage of logical operators.
  </para>

</section>
